    "industrial_process_notes": "Not a single synthesis route -- TPEs are unified by structure (microphase-separated hard/soft domains, or a rubber phase dispersed in a thermoplastic matrix) rather than chemistry. Major families: styrenic block copolymers (SBS/SEBS), thermoplastic polyurethanes (TPU), thermoplastic polyolefins (TPO, rubber-PP blends), thermoplastic vulcanizates (TPV, dynamically crosslinked rubber-PP blends), and copolyester/copolyamide TPEs (e.g. PEBA).",
